 //buttons: even with links, u can make them as buttons :<a href="" class="btn btn-lg btn-default disabled" role="button" >Home</a>
 //disabled is to disable the link
 
 <button type="submit" class="btn btn-danger" role="button" >Button</button>
 //other classes: btn-primary btn-sm btn-success btn-xs btn-lg btn-warning btn-link . btn: default button, btn-lg: large button btn-xs : extra small button btn-sm: small button
 //can use disabled="disabled" to disable a button.
 <input type="button" value="Info" class="btn btn-info">
 •btn-default for white
•btn-primary for dark blue
•btn-success for green
•btn-info for light blue
•btn-warning for orange
•btn-danger for red
 There are some more helper classes for buttons available: 
•btn-block will make the button span across the whole grid
•active will make the button look like it's currently clicked
•disabled will make the button unable to be clicked and appear faded.
 
